        "Professional Advisors in the ECS Advising, Counseling and Tutoring Center (ACT) can help with Lower-division major/pre-major planning, General Education & Graduation Requirements (GE/GR), and other advising-related topics. For contact information and drop-in hours, see ECS Student Success Center Advising .",
        "All full-time ME Faculty Members can provide advising to Undergraduates; you are not assigned a Faculty Advisor and may contact any Faculty Member you feel comfortable with to get advising. To get Office Hours and Zoom links for a Faculty Member, email the ME Department Office at me@csus.edu .",
        "Also see the Mechanical Engineering Faculty and Staff Directory for a listing of ME faculty with their office locations and contact information.",
        "ME students can also get assistance with GE/GR planning through advisors in the Academic Advising Center , located in Lassen Hall 1013.",
        "All ME undergraduates are required to complete an advising session each semester in order to register for the following semester.",
        "Prior to registration for Fall 2022 classes, you will receive an email providing instructions regarding your required advising session. A hold will be placed on your upcoming registration and this hold will be removed once you complete the required advising session."
